{"ts":"2026-06-27T02:36:11.951Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining GFF AI Branding**\n\nI've nailed down the GFF AI branding elements. We're rolling with `/footer/logo.svg` for the logo. \"GFF AI\" is the left text. The sub-brand is set up with three columns: \"GARAGE\" in red (#E4000F), \"FOUNDRY\" in white, and \"FACTORY\" in blue (#009DFF). The primary landing page background color will be #01.\n\n\n**Analyzing Login Page Premium**\n\nI'm now diving into the SecureLogin component to pinpoint ways to achieve a truly premium feel. I'm focusing on layout first, and I like the current 12-column grid. I think that we can elevate the design with subtle backdrops, clean typography, and motion effects to feel more premium, and I need to add visual and interactive elements.\n\n\n**Enhancing Login Background & Header**\n\nI'm now refining the SecureLogin component's visual appeal. The `bg-[#030303]` will be updated to match the landing page theme, ensuring consistency with either `#010101` or `#000000`. I'm also planning to add a premium background grid, or abstract light effects, to achieve an expensive, high-tech vibe. In addition, I will integrate a polished header overlay with the high-quality `/footer/logo.svg`.\n\n\n**Refining Motion & Layout**\n\nI'm now focusing on adding premium animations and layout refinements. I'm exploring an SVG-based handshake graphic or radar scan for a custom, strategic feel. I've confirmed we can use `motion` from `\"motion/react\"` and plan to implement subtle entrance animations, scan reveals, and micro-interactions. My priority is to achieve a high-end, uncluttered design, inspired by Lockheed Martin or Stripe AI, with perfect spacing and elegant borders while avoiding excessive badges.\n\n\n"}}
