{"ts":"2026-06-27T02:38:05.812Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Designing the Login Page**\n\nI'm pleased to share that the verification tools executed flawlessly. My focus has shifted to crafting a premium, custom login page within `components/portal/SecureLogin.tsx`. I'm committed to adhering to the UI Quality Constitution and integrating the page seamlessly with the existing landing page theme, specifically the pitch black background `#010101`.\n\n\n**Analyzing the Narrative**\n\nI'm now diving deep into the narrative. The login page embodies a secure gateway to a sophisticated AI platform. I'm focusing on weaving a compelling story: it's not just a login form but a portal to GFF AI's Sovereign Enclave, a zero-trust environment. The story is to use pre-configured \"Local Role Sandbox\" profiles for different granular dashboard boundaries. The visuals need to be on par with the role sandbox choice.\n\n\n**Visualizing the Security Process**\n\nI'm now visualizing the \"Handshake & Clearance Decryption Protocol\" sequence. The initial 5 seconds must clearly communicate entry into the secure GFF AI Enclave, along with login options and the sandbox's secure nature. I envision an electronic keycard terminal or access node visual, with a grid background and glowing aura. I'm focusing on an SVG-based \"Zero-Trust Handshake Connection Graphic\" showing the nodes involved.\n\n\n**Enhancing the Interaction**\n\nI'm now focused on making the login page feel dynamic and alive. Hovering over a Role Sandbox profile will update a clearance preview panel with real-time status tickers, visual cues, and an access blueprint. Clicking a role will trigger a pulse effect on the input fields with typing animations or rapid count, and mock encryption hash strings. Submitting the form will run a cinematic \"Decryption Protocol Sequence\" screen with a progress bar and a live visual radar scan.\n\n\n**Optimizing Login Interactions**\n\nI'm now integrating accessibility best practices: proper tab indices, customizable focus states, ARIA roles, and keyboard listener triggers. I've reviewed the imports in `SecureLogin.tsx`, and I'm exploring the `motion/react` library for high-performance transitions, confirming it's imported correctly as `\"motion\"`. I'll explore if it can be used for the transition effects.\n\n\n**Refining the Layout**\n\nI'm now prioritizing the layout of the login page. I've decided on a strategic division: a global frame with the GFF AI logo, tagline, and a back-to-home link. I'll include a subtle background grid with ambient red-and-blue glow. The main part of the design has two sections: a left panel for the secure gateway form and a right panel to provide a dynamic preview of the currently selected access role.\n\n\n**Implementing Interactive Elements**\n\nI'm now focusing on interactive elements. I'm adding custom floating labels and focus borders, plus a smooth eye icon for password visibility. Below the form, there's a terminal micro-console with live, mock security logs. The access button will have a glowing background ring on hover with arrow micro-interactions. Sleek, custom SSO icons for Enterprise Entra ID and Okta are coming next.\n\n\n**Visualizing Permissions Access**\n\nI'm now prioritizing the \"Access Blueprint\" preview. I'll render a mini grid of permission nodes that light up based on role access levels. This visual metaphor will provide an interactive overview for the user to understand available roles and their access levels. The user's role choice will instantly update the access blueprint. Upon logging in, a fullscreen \"Quantum Cryptographic Scan Radar\" will run, complete with terminal logs.\n\n\n**Structuring Permissions Display**\n\nI'm now deep-diving into the dynamic structuring of the Permission Matrix. I'm focusing on the `SecureLogin.tsx` file for a masterclass UI, ensuring beautiful, standard input fields. I am leveraging the `rolesList` object. I am working on the following roles: `client_admin`, `client_member`, `gff_admin`, `gff_operator`, and `finance_admin` and their appropriate access sections.\n\n\n**Mapping Access Permissions**\n\nI'm now focusing on a dynamic, live authorization map, leveraging `canAccessPortalSection` and `canAccessAdminSection`. My plan is to render permissions visually, in a grid of emerald-400 (authorized) or rose-5 chips. I'm building authorization maps for `finance_controller`, `support_agent`, and `viewer` roles, referencing \"Client Portal\" and \"Admin Panel\" sections. I'm organizing access for sections like \"Dashboard,\" \"Billing,\" \"Support,\" and others.\n\n\n**Refining the Background**\n\nI'm now refining the login page background. I'm implementing a pure CSS grid with subtle radial and linear gradients for a high-end feel. These color glows will add depth without external assets. I'm focusing on the effect with blue and red hues. Next, I plan to develop a dynamic SVG diagram to represent the zero-trust security handshake visually.\n\n\n**Implementing the Enclave**\n\nI'm now implementing the SecureLogin component, ensuring the preservation of existing functionality. I'm focusing on the integration of visual cues like glowing SVG lines and blinking pulses into the \"Sovereign Enclave\" design. My aim is to craft a visually striking and secure login experience. I'm making sure to implement authorization factors too.\n\n\n**Verifying Route Guards**\n\nI've confirmed that no changes are needed outside `components/portal/SecureLogin.tsx`, and that it is referenced as expected. I'm focusing now on the detailed design, starting with the background and global branding for a high-end feel.\n\n\n**Enhancing User Experience**\n\nI'm now integrating custom input cards with smooth keyboard navigation and precise focus outlines for enhanced usability. I'm focusing on adding an interactive password toggle and implementing mock encryption logs, which dynamically update with real-time security telemetry. Also, I am adding a \"bento-box\" authorization matrix which illustrates the access of different roles.\n\n**Crafting Visualizations**\n\nI'm now focusing on a high-fidelity SVG diagram to visually represent secure handshakes and cryptographic keys between system nodes. Also, I'm working on a cinema-quality radar/ring scanning screen as an overlay, complete with a rotating compass and custom symbols to visualize the authentication process.\n\n\n**Finalizing Implementation**\n\nI'm now prioritizing the completion of the `SecureLogin.tsx` component. I'm focusing on ensuring its functionality, verifying imports like `setPreviewSession`, `PreviewRole`, and the `useRouter` hook are correct. I'm also confirming that the `defaultRole` prop's logic behaves as expected for role assignments. The visual additions are being implemented.\n\n\n\n**Defining User Interface**\n\nI'm now defining the user interface with comprehensive state management. I'm expanding existing state variables like `selectedRole`, `authMethod`, `email`, `password`, `otpCode`, `showPassword`, `error`, `showForgot`, `showSupport`, `scanning`, and `scanStep` to support all functionality. I'm also reviewing `rolesList` in `SecureLogin.tsx` to ensure all user roles are covered. I found the following mock user roles: `client_admin`, `client_member`, `gff_admin`, and `gff_operator`.\n\n\n**Visualizing Key Handshakes**\n\nI'm now designing the custom SVG Connection Handshake diagram. I'll create an SVG showcasing three circles: Terminal (User), Gateway (GFF Crypt), and Memory (Enclave Shield). This will provide a clear visual representation of the secure handshake process. I'll also add mock security telemetry in real-time.\n\n\n**Designing Access Matrices**\n\nI'm now designing the Access Control Matrix in SVG and CSS, using animated connecting lines. I'm focusing on \"glowing bead\" animations for the lines and the visual breakdown of access levels using color-coded dots and corresponding section names. I am using a pure SVG and CSS approach for a lightweight, high-end look. My goal is to display each section's name, its access type (\"FULL ACCESS,\" \"READ ONLY,\" \"RESTRICTED\"), and corresponding dots (Red/Gray, Amber/Yellow, Green) to map authorizations.\n\n\n**Mapping Access Details**\n\nI'm now mapping out detailed permissions for an interactive access matrix. I'm focusing on \"Support Wire,\" \"Admin Oversight Panel - Clients & Users,\" and \"Admin Oversight Panel - Sovereign System Control.\" My goal is to build a highly responsive and visually compelling interactive chart. I'm envisioning the matrix rows dynamically lighting up or dimming to highlight granted and denied permissions, demonstrating the power of the frontend role preview.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T02:38:05.827Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"019nh3ig","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/components/portal/SecureLogin.tsx","new_text":"\"use client\";\n\nimport React, { useState, useEffect, useRef } from \"react\";\nimport { useRouter } from \"next/navigation\";\nimport Link from \"next/link\";\nimport { \n  Lock, Shield, Key, CheckCircle, RefreshCw, Layers, Eye, EyeOff, \n  Users, Cpu, FileText, HelpCircle, Fingerprint, ArrowRight, AlertCircle, X, Info, Terminal, Server, Globe, Database, Network\n} from \"lucide-react\";\nimport { setPreviewSession, PreviewRole, MOCK_PREVIEW_USERS } from \"@/lib/preview-auth\";\nimport { motion, AnimatePresence } from \"motion/react\";\n\nexport default function SecureLogin({ defaultRole }: { defaultRole?: string }) {\n  const router = useRouter();\n  \n  // Configure default active role state based on prop\n  const [selectedRole, setSelectedRole] = useState<PreviewRole>(\n    defaultRole === \"Administrator\" ? \"gff_admin\" : \"client_admin\"\n  );\n  \n  const [authMethod, setAuthMethod] = useState<\"credentials\" | \"otp\">(\"credentials\");\n  const [email, setEmail] = useState(\"\");\n  const [password, setPassword] = useState(\"\");\n  const [otpCode, setOtpCode] = useState(\"\");\n  const [showPassword, setShowPassword] = useState(false);\n  const [error, setError] = useState(\"\");\n  const [showForgot, setShowForgot] = useState(false);\n  const [showSupport, setShowSupport] = useState(false);\n  \n  // Cinematic transition sequence states\n  const [scanning, setScanning] = useState(false);\n  const [scanStep, setScanStep] = useState(0);\n  \n  // Security simulation terminal telemetry log lines\n  const [telemetryLogs, setTelemetryLogs] = useState<string[]>([]);\n  const consoleBottomRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);\n\n  const rolesList = [\n    { id: \"client_admin\" as PreviewRole, label: \"Client Admin\", clearance: \"L-3\", desc: \"Sovereign gateway owner\", icon: Users, color: \"text-[#009DFF]\" },\n    { id: \"client_member\" as PreviewRole, label: \"Client Member\", clearance: \"L-2\", desc: \"Model operator layer worker\", icon: Layers, color: \"text-blue-400\" },\n    { id: \"gff_admin\" as PreviewRole, label: \"GFF Admin\", clearance: \"L-5\", desc: \"Root platform superintendent\", icon: Shield, color: \"text-[#E4000F]\" },\n    { id: \"gff_operator\" as PreviewRole, label: \"GFF Operator\", clearance: \"L-4\", desc: \"Model architecture controller\", icon: Cpu, color: \"text-purple-400\" },\n    { id: \"finance_admin\" as PreviewRole, label: \"Finance Admin\", clearance: \"L-3\", desc: \"Epoch financial ledger auditor\", icon: FileText, color: \"text-emerald-400\" },\n    { id: \"support_agent\" as PreviewRole, label: \"Support Agent\", clearance: \"L-3\", desc: \"SLA wire operations specialist\", icon: HelpCircle, color: \"text-orange-400\" },\n    { id: \"viewer\" as PreviewRole, label: \"Auditor (Viewer)\", clearance: \"L-1\", desc: \"Read-only observer node\", icon: Eye, color: \"text-zinc-400\" },\n  ];\n\n  // Auto-populate form details when role profile updates\n  useEffect(() => {\n    const mockUser = MOCK_PREVIEW_USERS[selectedRole];\n    if (mockUser) {\n      setEmail(mockUser.email);\n      setPassword(\"••••••••••••\");\n      setOtpCode(\"102486\");\n      \n      // Seed initial cryptographic simulation logs\n      const generatedHash = Math.random().toString(16).substring(2, 10).toUpperCase();\n      const logs = [\n        `[INIT] Handshake request received from node terminal.`,\n        `[IDENTITY] Resolved profile context: ${mockUser.role.toUpperCase()}`,\n        `[SSL/TLS] Session handshake initiated via SHA-256 cipher (ECDHE_RSA_AES_128_GCM).`,\n        `[SECURITY] Clearance key resolved: ${mockUser.clearance.split(\" \")[2] || \"L-3\"}-${generatedHash}`,\n        `[SANDBOX] Memory enclave isolated. Sandbox state: READY.`\n      ];\n      setTelemetryLogs(logs);\n    }\n  }, [selectedRole]);\n\n  // Append new simulation logs when user types\n  const handleInputChange = (field: string, val: string) => {\n    if (field === \"email\") {\n      setEmail(val);\n      if (val.length % 3 === 0) {\n        logTelemetry(`[INPUT] Term buffer parsed: ${val.substring(0, 15)}${val.length > 15 ? \"...\" : \"\"} (resolving DNS)`);\n      }\n    } else if (field === \"password\") {\n      setPassword(val);\n      if (val.length % 2 === 0) {\n        const hashPart = Math.random().toString(16).substring(2, 6).toUpperCase();\n        logTelemetry(`[CRYPT] Salted passphrase vector: SHA-512_SALT_${hashPart}`);\n      }\n    } else if (field === \"otp\") {\n      setOtpCode(val);\n      if (val.length === 6) {\n        logTelemetry(`[OTP] Multi-factor authentication block complete. Ready for clearance verification.`);\n      }\n    }\n  };\n\n  const logTelemetry = (msg: string) => {\n    setTelemetryLogs(prev => [...prev.slice(-12), msg]);\n  };\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (consoleBottomRef.current) {\n      consoleBottomRef.current.scrollIntoView({ behavior: \"smooth\" });\n    }\n  }, [telemetryLogs]);\n\n  // Authentication submission routine with cinematic radar scan sequence\n  const handleAuthenticate = async () => {\n    setScanning(true);\n    setScanStep(0);\n    \n    // Smooth step updates for cinematic overlay\n    const stepIntervals = [250, 300, 350, 400];\n    for (let i = 0; i < stepIntervals.length; i++) {\n      await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, stepIntervals[i]));\n      setScanStep(prev => prev + 1);\n    }\n    \n    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 400));\n    setScanning(false);\n    \n    // Commit simulated preview session variables\n    setPreviewSession(selectedRole);\n    \n    // Route to appropriate core administration dashboard based on clearance level\n    const isGffStaff = !selectedRole.startsWith(\"client_\");\n    router.push(isGffStaff ? \"/admin/dashboard\" : \"/portal/dashboard\");\n  };\n\n  const handleSubmit = (e: React.FormEvent) => {\n    e.preventDefault();\n    handleAuthenticate();\n  };\n\n  const currentMockUser = MOCK_PREVIEW_USERS[selectedRole];\n  const activeRoleObj = rolesList.find(r => r.id === selectedRole) || rolesList[0];\n\n  const scanMessages = [\n    \"Establishing zero-trust gateway handshake protocol...\",\n    \"Isolating browser session within local memory sandbox container...\",\n    \"Exchanging SHA-256 secure tokens with crypt node gateway...\",\n    \"Provisioning administrative clearance keys in sovereign database...\",\n    \"Clearance successfully decrypted. Granting portal dashboard access...\"\n  ];\n\n  // Helper mapping to generate the real-time visual RBAC permissions matrix\n  const getPermissionStatus = (role: PreviewRole, module: string) => {\n    // GFF Superuser has total administrative master clearance over everything\n    if (role === \"gff_admin\") {\n      return { status: \"AUTHORIZED\", color: \"text-emerald-400 border-emerald-500/20 bg-emerald-500/5\", dot: \"bg-emerald-400\" };\n    }\n    \n    // Read-only observer/auditor profile\n    if (role === \"viewer\") {\n      const isReadOnlyModule = [\"Core Terminal\", \"Sovereign Control\", \"AI Governance\"].includes(module);\n      if (isReadOnlyModule) {\n        return { status: \"READ ONLY\", color: \"text-amber-400 border-amber-500/20 bg-amber-500/5\", dot: \"bg-amber-400\" };\n      }\n      return { status: \"RESTRICTED\", color: \"text-zinc-600 border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950/20\", dot: \"bg-zinc-700\" };\n    }\n\n    // Role-specific evaluation mapping for dashboard modules\n    switch (module) {\n      case \"Core Terminal\":\n        return [\"client_admin\", \"client_member\", \"gff_operator\", \"finance_admin\", \"support_agent\"].includes(role)\n          ? { status: \"AUTHORIZED\", color: \"text-emerald-400 border-emerald-500/20 bg-emerald-500/5\", dot: \"bg-emerald-400\" }\n          : { status: \"RESTRICTED\", color: \"text-zinc-600 border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950/20\", dot: \"bg-zinc-700\" };\n      \n      case \"AI Operations\":\n        return [\"client_admin\", \"client_member\", \"gff_operator\"].includes(role)\n          ? { status: \"AUTHORIZED\", color: \"text-emerald-400 border-emerald-500/20 bg-emerald-500/5\", dot: \"bg-emerald-400\" }\n          : { status: \"RESTRICTED\", color: \"text-zinc-600 border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950/20\", dot: \"bg-zinc-700\" };\n      \n      case \"AI Governance\":\n        return [\"client_admin\", \"client_member\", \"gff_operator\"].includes(role)\n          ? { status: \"AUTHORIZED\", color: \"text-emerald-400 border-emerald-500/20 bg-emerald-500/5\", dot: \"bg-emerald-400\" }\n          : { status: \"RESTRICTED\", color: \"text-zinc-600 border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950/20\", dot: \"bg-zinc-700\" };\n      \n      case \"Financial Ledger\":\n        return [\"client_admin\", \"finance_admin\"].includes(role)\n          ? { status: \"AUTHORIZED\", color: \"text-emerald-400 border-emerald-500/20 bg-emerald-500/5\", dot: \"bg-emerald-400\" }\n          : { status: \"RESTRICTED\", color: \"text-zinc-600 border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950/20\", dot: \"bg-zinc-700\" };\n      \n      case \"Sovereign Control\":\n        return [\"gff_operator\"].includes(role)\n          ? { status: \"AUTHORIZED\", color: \"text-emerald-400 border-emerald-500/20 bg-emerald-500/5\", dot: \"bg-emerald-400\" }\n          : { status: \"RESTRICTED\", color: \"text-zinc-600 border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950/20\", dot: \"bg-zinc-700\" };\n      \n      case \"Support Enclave\":\n        return [\"client_admin\", \"client_member\", \"support_agent\"].includes(role)\n          ? { status: \"AUTHORIZED\", color: \"text-emerald-400 border-emerald-500/20 bg-emerald-500/5\", dot: \"bg-emerald-400\" }\n          : { status: \"RESTRICTED\", color: \"text-zinc-600 border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950/20\", dot: \"bg-zinc-700\" };\n      \n      case \"Users Directory\":\n        return [\"support_agent\"].includes(role)\n          ? { status: \"AUTHORIZED\", color: \"text-emerald-400 border-emerald-500/20 bg-emerald-500/5\", dot: \"bg-emerald-400\" }\n          : { status: \"RESTRICTED\", color: \"text-zinc-600 border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950/20\", dot: \"bg-zinc-700\" };\n          \n      default:\n        return { status: \"RESTRICTED\", color: \"text-zinc-600 border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950/20\", dot: \"bg-zinc-700\" };\n    }\n  };\n\n  const matrixModules = [\n    \"Core Terminal\",\n    \"AI Operations\",\n    \"AI Governance\",\n    \"Financial Ledger\",\n    \"Sovereign Control\",\n    \"Support Enclave\",\n    \"Users Directory\"\n  ];\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"min-h-screen w-full bg-[#010101] text-zinc-100 flex flex-col items-center justify-center relative px-4 py-8 md:py-16 select-none overflow-hidden font-sans\">\n      \n      {/* Premium Ambient Background Grid & Radial Glow elements */}\n      <div className=\"absolute inset-0 z-0 pointer-events-none opacity-40\">\n        <div \n          className=\"absolute inset-0\"\n          style={{\n            backgroundImage: `\n              radial-gradient(circle at 10% 20%, rgba(228, 0, 15, 0.04) 0%, transparent 45%),\n              radial-gradient(circle at 90% 80%, rgba(0, 157, 255, 0.04) 0%, transparent 45%),\n              linear-gradient(rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.005) 1px, transparent 1px),\n              linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.005) 1px, transparent 1px)\n            `,\n            backgroundSize: \"100% 100%, 100% 100%, 45px 45px, 45px 45px\"\n          }}\n        />\n        <div className=\"absolute top-1/2 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-[600px] h-[600px] bg-gradient-to-r from-[#009DFF]/3 to-[#E4000F]/3 rounded-full blur-[140px] pointer-events-none\" />\n      </div>\n\n      {/* Global Minimalist Header Bar */}\n      <header className=\"absolute top-0 left-0 right-0 h-20 w-full z-20 flex justify-between items-center px-6 lg:px-16 border-b border-white/5 bg-black/20 backdrop-blur-md\">\n        <Link href=\"/\" className=\"flex items-center gap-2.5 hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity\">\n          <img src=\"/footer/logo.svg\" alt=\"GFF AI Logo\" className=\"w-10 h-10 object-contain\" />\n          <div className=\"flex flex-col text-left\">\n            <span className=\"text-white text-base font-semibold tracking-wider leading-none\">GFF AI</span>\n            <span className=\"text-[7.5px] font-bold tracking-[0.1em] mt-1 text-zinc-400\">\n              <span className=\"text-[#E4000F]\">GARAGE</span> | FOUNDRY | <span className=\"text-[#009DFF]\">FACTORY</span>\n            </span>\n          </div>\n        </Link>\n        \n        <Link \n          href=\"/\" \n          className=\"text-xs font-mono font-bold tracking-widest text-zinc-400 hover:text-white transition-colors flex items-center gap-1.5 focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-[#009DFF] rounded px-2 py-1\"\n        >\n          ← RETURN TO WEBSITE\n        </Link>\n      </header>\n\n      {/* Main Container Layout */}\n      <div className=\"w-full max-w-[1100px] z-10 mt-14\">\n        <div className=\"text-center space-y-2 mb-8\">\n          <h1 className=\"text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold tracking-wider font-sans text-white uppercase\">Sovereign Portal Authorization</h1>\n          <p className=\"text-xs text-zinc-400 max-w-lg mx-auto leading-relaxed\">\n            Verify credentials to decrypt local administrative workspaces. Select a sandbox identity profile to preview role-based features dynamically.\n          </p>\n        </div>\n\n        <div className=\"border border-zinc-800/80 bg-zinc-950/45 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden shadow-2xl backdrop-blur-xl relative\">\n          <AnimatePresence mode=\"wait\">\n            {!scanning ? (\n              <motion.div \n                key=\"login-grid\"\n                initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 15 }}\n                animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}\n                exit={{ opacity: 0, y: -15 }}\n                transition={{ duration: 0.35, ease: \"easeOut\" }}\n                className=\"grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 divide-y lg:divide-y-0 lg:divide-x divide-zinc-800/60\"\n              >\n                {/* Left Panel: Enclave Credentials Gateway */}\n                <div className=\"lg:col-span-6 p-6 md:p-8 space-y-6\">\n                  {/* Gate Title Header */}\n                  <div className=\"flex justify-between items-center pb-3 border-b border-zinc-900\">\n                    <div>\n                      <h2 className=\"text-xs font-bold text-zinc-300 uppercase tracking-widest font-mono flex items-center gap-1.5\">\n                        <Shield className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5 text-[#009DFF]\" /> Cryptographic Keycard\n                      </h2>\n                      <p className=\"text-[10px] text-zinc-500 mt-0.5\">Initialize secure local handshake protocols.</p>\n                    </div>\n                    <div className=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 px-2 py-0.5 rounded bg-emerald-500/5 border border-emerald-500/20 text-emerald-400 text-[8px] font-mono font-bold tracking-widest\">\n                      <span className=\"h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-emerald-400 animate-pulse\" />\n                      ENCLAVE ONLINE\n                    </div>\n                  </div>\n\n                  {/* High-End Tab Select Method Toggle */}\n                  <div className=\"flex bg-zinc-950/90 p-1 rounded-lg border border-zinc-900\" role=\"tablist\" aria-label=\"Authentication Method\">\n                    <button\n                      type=\"button\"\n                      role=\"tab\"\n                      aria-selected={authMethod === \"credentials\"}\n                      onClick={() => { setAuthMethod(\"credentials\"); setError(\"\"); logTelemetry(\"[TAB] Switched method to Secure Keycard (Credentials).\"); }}\n                      className={`flex-1 py-1.5 rounded text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest transition-all cursor-pointer focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-[#009DFF] ${\n                        authMethod === \"credentials\" \n                          ? \"bg-zinc-900 text-white shadow-sm border border-zinc-800/60\" \n                          : \"text-zinc-500 hover:text-zinc-300 border border-transparent\"\n                      }`}\n                    >\n                      SECURE KEYCARD\n                    </button>\n                    <button\n                      type=\"button\"\n                      role=\"tab\"\n                      aria-selected={authMethod === \"otp\"}\n                      onClick={() => { setAuthMethod(\"otp\"); setError(\"\"); logTelemetry(\"[TAB] Switched method to Token Code (MFA OTP).\"); }}\n                      className={`flex-1 py-1.5 rounded text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-widest transition-all cursor-pointer focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-[#009DFF] ${\n                        authMethod === \"otp\" \n                          ? \"bg-zinc-900 text-white shadow-sm border border-zinc-800/60\" \n                          : \"text-zinc-500 hover:text-zinc-300 border border-transparent\"\n                      }`}\n                    >\n                      TOKEN CODE (OTP)\n                    </button>\n                  </div>\n\n                  {/* Authentication Form fields */}\n                  <form onSubmit={handleSubmit} className=\"space-y-4\">\n                    <div className=\"space-y-1.5\">\n                      <label htmlFor=\"auth-email\" className=\"text-[9.5px] font-mono text-zinc-400 uppercase tracking-widest block font-bold\">\n                        Enterprise Email Address\n                      </label>\n                      <input\n                        id=\"auth-email\"\n                        type=\"email\"\n                        value={email}\n                        onChange={(e) => handleInputChange(\"email\", e.target.value)}\n                        placeholder=\"employee@gff.ai\"\n                        className=\"w-full h-10 px-3 rounded-lg bg-zinc-950/80 border border-zinc-800 focus:border-[#009DFF] focus:ring-1 focus:ring-[#009DFF] text-zinc-200 text-xs placeholder-zinc-700 transition-all outline-none font-mono focus:bg-zinc-950\"\n                        required\n                        aria-required=\"true\"\n                      />\n                    </div>\n\n                    {authMethod === \"credentials\" ? (\n                      <div className=\"space-y-1.5\">\n                        <div className=\"flex justify-between items-center\">\n                          <label htmlFor=\"auth-pass\" className=\"text-[9.5px] font-mono text-zinc-400 uppercase tracking-widest block font-bold\">\n                            Passphrase Key\n                          </label>\n                          <button\n                            type=\"button\"\n                            onClick={() => setShowForgot(true)}\n                            className=\"text-[9px] text-zinc-500 hover:text-[#009DFF] transition-colors focus:outline-none cursor-pointer hover:underline\"\n                          >\n                            Forgot Key?\n                          </button>\n                        </div>\n                        <div className=\"relative\">\n                          <input\n                            id=\"auth-pass\"\n                            type={showPassword ? \"text\" : \"password\"}\n                            value={password}\n                            onChange={(e) => handleInputChange(\"password\", e.target.value)}\n                            placeholder=\"••••••••••••\"\n                            className=\"w-full h-10 pl-3 pr-10 rounded-lg bg-zinc-950/80 border border-zinc-800 focus:border-[#009DFF] focus:ring-1 focus:ring-[#009DFF] text-zinc-200 text-xs placeholder-zinc-700 transition-all outline-none font-mono tracking-widest focus:bg-zinc-950\"\n                            required\n                            aria-required=\"true\"\n                          />\n                          <button\n                            type=\"button\"\n                            onClick={() => setShowPassword(!showPassword)}\n                            className=\"absolute right-3 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-zinc-500 hover:text-zinc-300 transition-colors focus:outline-none cursor-pointer\"\n                            aria-label={showPassword ? \"Hide password\" : \"Show password\"}\n                          >\n                            {showPassword ? <EyeOff className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5\" /> : <Eye className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5\" />}\n                          </button>\n                        </div>\n                      </div>\n                    ) : (\n                      <div className=\"space-y-1.5\">\n                        <div className=\"flex justify-between items-center\">\n                          <label htmlFor=\"auth-otp\" className=\"text-[9.5px] font-mono text-zinc-400 uppercase tracking-widest block font-bold\">\n                            Multi-Factor OTP Code\n                          </label>\n                          <button\n                            type=\"button\"\n                            onClick={() => {\n                              logTelemetry(\"[SYS] Requested simulation OTP broadcast. Code generated: 102486\");\n                              setOtpCode(\"102486\");\n                            }}\n                            className=\"text-[9px] text-zinc-500 hover:text-[#009DFF] transition-colors focus:outline-none cursor-pointer\"\n                          >\n                            Send OTP Broadcast?\n                          </button>\n                        </div>\n                        <input\n                          id=\"auth-otp\"\n                          type=\"text\"\n                          value={otpCode}\n                          onChange={(e) => handleInputChange(\"otp\", e.target.value)}\n                          placeholder=\"102486\"\n                          maxLength={6}\n                          className=\"w-full h-10 px-3 rounded-lg bg-zinc-950/80 border border-zinc-800 focus:border-[#009DFF] focus:ring-1 focus:ring-[#009DFF] text-zinc-200 text-xs placeholder-zinc-700 transition-all outline-none font-mono tracking-[0.4em] text-center focus:bg-zinc-950\"\n                          required\n                          aria-required=\"true\"\n                        />\n                      </div>\n                    )}\n\n                    {error && (\n                      <div className=\"p-3 bg-rose-950/20 border border-rose-900/35 text-rose-400 rounded-lg text-xs flex items-center gap-2 animate-pulse\">\n                        <AlertCircle className=\"w-4 h-4 shrink-0\" />\n                        <span>{error}</span>\n                      </div>\n                    )}\n\n                    <button\n                      type=\"submit\"\n                      className=\"w-full h-10 rounded-lg bg-[#009DFF] hover:bg-[#0086db] text-black font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-widest flex items-center justify-center gap-2 cursor-pointer active:scale-[0.98] transition-all hover:shadow-[0_0_20px_rgba(0,157,255,0.25)] focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#009DFF] focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-offset-black\"\n                    >\n                      <Lock className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5\" /> Initialize Cryptographic Connection\n                    </button>\n                  </form>\n\n                  {/* Simulated Telemetry Logging System (Micro console terminal) */}\n                  <div className=\"space-y-1.5 pt-1\">\n                    <div className=\"flex items-center justify-between text-[8px] text-zinc-500 uppercase font-mono tracking-widest font-bold\">\n                      <span className=\"flex items-center gap-1\"><Terminal className=\"w-2.5 h-2.5\" /> Cryptographic Handshake Telemetry</span>\n                      <span>ACTIVE SOCKET</span>\n                    </div>\n                    <div className=\"h-28 rounded-lg bg-zinc-950 border border-zinc-900/90 p-2.5 font-mono text-[9px] text-zinc-400 overflow-y-auto space-y-1 select-text scrollbar-thin scrollbar-thumb-zinc-800\">\n                      {telemetryLogs.map((log, idx) => (\n                        <div key={idx} className=\"leading-relaxed border-l border-zinc-800 pl-2\">\n                          <span className=\"text-zinc-600\">[{new Date().toLocaleTimeString().split(\" \")[0]}]</span>{\" \"}\n                          <span className={log.includes(\"[ERROR]\") ? \"text-rose-400\" : log.includes(\"[INIT]\") || log.includes(\"[IDENTITY]\") ? \"text-[#009DFF] font-semibold\" : \"text-zinc-300\"}>\n                            {log}\n                          </span>\n                        </div>\n                      ))}\n                      <div ref={consoleBottomRef} />\n                    </div>\n                  </div>\n\n                  {/* SSO Connectors */}\n                  <div className=\"space-y-2\">\n                    <div className=\"flex items-center text-[8px] text-zinc-500 uppercase font-bold tracking-widest\">\n                      <span className=\"h-[1px] bg-zinc-900 flex-1 mr-2.5\" />\n                      <span>Federated Enclaves</span>\n                      <span className=\"h-[1px] bg-zinc-900 flex-1 ml-2.5\" />\n                    </div>\n                    <div className=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-2.5\">\n                      <button\n                        type=\"button\"\n                        onClick={() => {\n                          logTelemetry(\"[SSO] Requesting Entra ID challenge payload...\");\n                          alert(\"SSO handshaking: Connecting browser to Azure AD/Entra ID sandbox portal...\");\n                        }}\n                        className=\"flex items-center justify-center gap-1.5 py-2 px-3 rounded-lg border border-zinc-800/80 bg-zinc-950/20 hover:bg-zinc-900/40 text-[10.5px] font-mono font-semibold text-zinc-300 transition-all hover:border-zinc-700 cursor-pointer focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-[#009DFF]\"\n                      >\n                        <svg className=\"w-3 h-3 shrink-0\" viewBox=\"0 0 23 23\" fill=\"currentColor\">\n                          <path d=\"M0 0h11v11H0z\" fill=\"#f25022\"/>\n                          <path d=\"M12 0h11v11H12z\" fill=\"#7fba00\"/>\n                          <path d=\"M0 12h11v11H0z\" fill=\"#00a4ef\"/>\n                          <path d=\"M12 12h11v11H12z\" fill=\"#ffb900\"/>\n                        </svg>\n                        <span>ENTRA ID</span>\n                      </button>\n                      <button\n                        type=\"button\"\n                        onClick={() => {\n                          logTelemetry(\"[SSO] Requesting Okta security assertion assertion...\");\n                          alert(\"SSO handshaking: Initializing secure Okta login portal simulated exchange...\");\n                        }}\n                        className=\"flex items-center justify-center gap-1.5 py-2 px-3 rounded-lg border border-zinc-800/80 bg-zinc-950/20 hover:bg-zinc-900/40 text-[10.5px] font-mono font-semibold text-zinc-300 transition-all hover:border-zinc-700 cursor-pointer focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-[#009DFF]\"\n                      >\n                        <svg className=\"w-3 h-3 shrink-0 text-[#007dc1]\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"currentColor\">\n                          <path d=\"M12 0C5.37 0 0 5.37 0 12s5.37 12 12 12 12-5.37 12-12S18.63 0 12 0zm0 18c-3.31 0-6-2.69-6-6s2.69-6 6-6 6 2.69 6 6-2.69 6-6 6z\"/>\n                        </svg>\n                        <span>OKTA SSO</span>\n                      </button>\n                    </div>\n                    <div className=\"flex justify-between items-center text-[10px] text-zinc-500/80 pt-1\">\n                      <span className=\"font-mono text-[9px]\">Sovereign Enclave GFF_0x7FFA</span>\n                      <button\n                        type=\"button\"\n                        onClick={() => setShowSupport(true)}\n                        className=\"hover:text-[#009DFF] hover:underline flex items-center gap-1 transition-all focus:outline-none cursor-pointer\"\n                      >\n                        <HelpCircle className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5\" /> Secure Support Relay\n                      </button>\n                    </div>\n                  </div>\n                </div>\n\n                {/* Right Panel: Interactive Local Role Sandbox */}\n                <div className=\"lg:col-span-6 p-6 md:p-8 bg-zinc-950/20 flex flex-col justify-between space-y-6\">\n                  <div className=\"space-y-4\">\n                    <div className=\"space-y-1\">\n                      <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2\">\n                        <Terminal className=\"w-4 h-4 text-[#009DFF]\" />\n                        <h3 className=\"text-xs font-bold text-white font-mono uppercase tracking-wider\">Local Role Sandbox Preview</h3>\n                      </div>\n                      <p className=\"text-[10.5px] text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed font-sans\">\n                        Select an administrative role profile to pre-configure security keys and immediately explore RBAC boundaries in the client portal or oversight console.\n                      </p>\n                    </div>\n\n                    {/* Clean Alert Box warning */}\n                    <div className=\"p-3 rounded-xl border border-[#009DFF]/15 bg-[#009DFF]/5 text-zinc-300 text-[10.5px] leading-relaxed space-y-1\">\n                      <div className=\"flex items-center gap-1.5 font-bold text-[#009DFF] uppercase tracking-wider font-mono text-[9px]\">\n                        <Info className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5 shrink-0\" />\n                        DEVELOPME