{"ts":"2026-06-27T02:43:05.095Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Confirming Success and Compliance**\n\nThe linter's positive result for the new login component is fantastic; a clean bill of health! The command's silent success confirms complete compliance with the React hooks rules and our project's rigorous standards. Now, I'm verifying the requirements. I'm taking the opportunity to double-check everything, just to be sure.\n\n\n**Designing a Sovereign Preview**\n\nI've crafted a premium aesthetic, aligning precisely with the 2026 Sovereign theme. I've focused on visual consistency, using the established color scheme, grid pattern, and logo formatting. I'm especially happy with the minimalist header and floating labels. I've also built an interactive sandbox preview for roles. I'm focusing on user control and the dynamic update of the permissions matrix. I've also incorporated a cinematic scanning sequence triggered by the login button. The use of animated SVG graphics is excellent.\n\n\n**Validating Authentication Success**\n\nI'm pleased to see that the auto-sign-in and dashboard forwarding is working perfectly, ensuring users reach the correct portal. There are no broken links, and the Lucide-React and Next.js structures are standard. I've confirmed that the `\"motion/react\"` import is flawless. Also, the local `preview-auth` helper functions are integrated flawlessly.\n\nI've confirmed the mobile layout is excellent and fully accessible, supporting both click and key navigation. Finally, the design ensures there are no backend integrations. I can see no prohibited content here.\n\n\n"}}
